description: Euler phi function applied thrice to n.
links: Boris Putievskiy, Transformations [Of] Integer Sequences And Pairing Functions, arXiv preprint arXiv:1212.2732, 2012.
example: n=163: the successive iterates of Euler totient function are 163,162,54,18,6,2,1. The 4th term is 18, when Phi was applied 3 times. So a(163)=18.
author: _Labos Elemer_
